**4 PILLARS OF OOPS.......

1.ENCAPSULATION:-> Wrapping up of data into a single unit.
   Example- Class.

2.ABSTRACTION:-> Only visible importatnt information and hide their implementation.
   Example- Access Modifier.

3.POLYMORPHISM:-> When one person has many forms.
   Example- '+'Operator.

           COMPILE TIME                       RUN TIME
   -> Function overloading          -> Virtual function
   -> Operator Overloading       

4.INHERITANCE:-> When wild class inherit properties from their parent class.

->Single Inheritance:1 Parent & 1 Child.
->Multilevel: Grandfather->Father->Child.
->Multiple: Multi parent & 1 child.
->Heirarchical: 1 parent & multiple child.
->Hybrid: Combination of any 2 or 3 inheritance.

                                                ***ABSTRACTION AND ENCAPSULATION CODE IN CPP:-

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
//ABSTRACTION & ENCAPSULATION

class student{
    private:
    //properties
    string name;
    int age;
    int roll_no;

    public:
    void setter(string n,int a,int r )
    {
        name = n;
        age = a;
        roll_no = r;
    }
    int getter()
    {
        return age;
    }
};

int main(){
    student obj;
    obj.setter("NAMAN",22,1072);
    cout<<obj.getter();
}

                                                    **POLYMORPHISM IN CPP:-

***FUNCTION OVERLOADING:-

#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

//polymorphism : ability of an object to take many form.

class student{
    public:
    int length;
    int breadth;

 //function overloading : same function name with different parameters.

    public:
    int area(int l,int r){
        return l*r;
    }

    int area(int r){
        return r*r;
    }

};

int main(){
    student obj;
    cout<<"Area of rectangle :"<<obj.area(10,5)<<endl;
    cout<<"Area of square :"<<obj.area(5)<<endl;
    return 0;
}
